Final Reminder for Meals:
Greetings Williamson Families, This message is to let you know that all students Pre-k through grade 12 are able to receive breakfast and lunch for free until the end of 2020. Please sign up for the survey if you want meals on the days your child is not at school. You only need to fill out the survey once for this 10 week marking period. Attention drivers that need the NYS 5-Hour Pre-licensing Course:

NYS - 5hr. Pre-licensing Course (Online and Live via Zoom)
Completion of this course earns the student the MV-278 Certificate. This certificate is required to schedule the NYS Road Test.
Cost is $40

The next scheduled classes are on Saturday, September 12 (8 AM - 1 PM) and Thursday September 17 (4 - 9 PM).

Be sure to enter your information carefully and make sure to open the link in the form for the Course Requirements & Details Document
The Student Manual for the course is also attached to the document if you would like to download it or print before the class. This is not required.

post_text: Williamson welcomes Marygrace Mazzullo as our next Superintendent of Schools. Her career pathway started at Pavilion Central School District where she was a secondary level English Language Arts teacher. She then served as the district's Director of Curriculum, prior to moving into the position of Elementary Principal at York Central School District. Marygrace then accepted the role as the Director of ELA at Webster Central School District's Central Office. Mrs. Mazzullo has worked for Williamson in the role of Assistant Superintendent for Instruction since 2014. We know that Mrs. Mazzullo's experiences will serve our schools and community well as she begins her tenure as the Superintendent of Williamson Central School District. Congratulations, Mrs. Mazzullo!

The following communication was sent home to families this evening:

Good afternoon,

This is Dr. Macaluso calling to inform you of a survey for families to complete on their feelings regarding the reopening of school.

The initial feedback on school reopening will take less than two minutes, and the survey as a whole will take less than five minutes. Your survey will help us gather insight and understanding first on your perspective on reopening school and then on the impact of virtual learning over the past few months. While guidance from NYS and directives from our own local Public Health Department are governing forces in our decision making, we would like to make sure that we are as inclusive and as sensitive as we can be to the needs of the families we serve.

To provide feedback on your feelings on school reopening, please complete the survey. The survey can be found in your email, on social media, and our website.
https://www.surveygizmo.com/s3/5657688/Parent-Voice-Survey-2020

Update regarding the School Budget Vote & Board of Education Election:

Executive Order No. 202.39:
Regarding school elections, school districts must now accept ballots sent via U.S. mail until Tuesday, June 16. However, the cutoff for hand-delivered ballots remains 5 p.m. tomorrow (Tuesday, June 9).

"Any receptacle used for hand delivery of absentee ballots in such election shall be closed and removed at 5 p.m. on June 9, 2020," the order states. "The ballots therein shall remain unopened pending delivery of mailed ballots, and shall be removed and canvassed after 5 p.m. on June 16, 2020."

Any questions, please call the District Office and speak to the District Clerk at 315-589-9661.

post_text:
May 1, 2020 Message from Dr. Macaluso:

Dear Williamson Families,

This is Dr. Macaluso writing to inform you that the Governor announced today that all New York schools will be closed through the end of 2019- 2020 school year. At this point there are many unanswered questions and we are awaiting guidance from the State Education Department so we can put a plan in place and get you answers. For now, we will continue with remote learning as we have been doing. I will have more information regarding a modified school calendar once we receive guidance from the state.

I want to thank you all for doing your part in keeping everyone safe and for keeping the learning going during this uncertain time. One thing I can say for certain, is that we all miss having our buildings active and seeing your smiling faces every day. We can help to control this pandemic, please be sure that you are doing your part to maintain social distancing and to stay safe and healthy.

Enjoy some sunshine tomorrow and have a great night . . .

For now, we will continue with remote learning as we have been doing. I will have more information regarding a modified school calendar once we receive guidance from the state.

I want to thank you all for doing your part in keeping everyone safe and for keeping the learning going during this uncertain time. One thing I can say for certain, is that we all miss having our buildings active and seeing your smiling faces every day. We can help to control this pandemic, please be sure that you are doing your part to maintain social distancing and to stay safe and healthy.

Enjoy some sunshine tomorrow and have a great night . . .

Meal distribution information for April 27 - May 1:

Good afternoon,

This is Dr. Macaluso, writing to inform you of the new survey for meals for the week of April 27 ‚Äì May 1, meal distribution is for Williamson students in grade UPK-12. ONLY fill out the survey below to let us know if you need meals provided for your students. Meal pick up will be Monday ‚Äì Friday from 11am to 12:30pm at the High School Cafeteria Patio Door. Meals will include a lunch for that day and breakfast for the following day. Anyone is able to pick up the meals for your student. If you or a designee are ABSOLUTELY unable to pick up meals due to transportation constraints, we have delivery on a limited basis, you will make that request on the survey. Please fill out the survey by Friday, April 17 at 12pm. You must fill out the survey each week. Any questions, please contact the Superintendent‚Äôs Office at 315-589-9661 and leave a message.

The survey can be found on our district website, in your email, and social media.

Thank you and stay healthy.

https://forms.gle/GqLD8nkcJxV92W3r9

Due April 20, 2020 by 5:00 pm

Petitions to nominate candidates for a seat on the Williamson Central School District Board of Education are now available in the District Office, 4184 Miller Street, Williamson, NY. Petitions and candidate information may be picked up in the office between 8:00 A.M. and 4:00 P.M. Petitions must be filed no later than Monday, April 20, 2020 at 5:00 P.M.

Board of Education members must meet the following qualifications:
‚Ä¢ Citizen of the United States
‚Ä¢ Eighteen (18) year of age
‚Ä¢ Able to read and write
‚Ä¢ Residency in the Williamson Central School District for at least one (1) year prior to the election
‚Ä¢ Cannot be an employee of the Williamson Central School District

The following vacancies are to be filled in the upcoming election:

(2) Three year terms currently held by Mrs. Angela DeFisher & Mr. Robert Wendler

More information can be found on our website https://www.williamsoncentral.org.

We continue to hear that there is a need for school aged child care in Williamson. We are asking those families who have elementary level students attending Williamson to help us investigate the childcare need/want. Please take a few minutes to complete this Childcare Survey. We will use this information to help us determine whether or not a district provided after school child care program is feasible. Thank you!

After School Childcare @ Williamson Elementary
text:
This past year, we tried to start a YMCA before and after school program at Williamson and did not have enough participation to sustain it. We continue to hear that there is a need for school aged child care in Williamson. We are asking those families who have elementary level students attending Williamson to help us investigate the childcare need/want. Please take a few minutes to complete this Childcare Survey. We will use this information to help us determine whether or not a district provided after school child care program is feasible. Thank you!

post_text:
We would like to introduce and welcome our new School Resource Officer, Deputy Lacey Hendershot! She will start on January 6, 2020.

Here is her bio:
I am Deputy Lacey Hendershot with the Wayne County Sheriff's Office. I was born and raised in Clyde and went to Clyde Savannah. I graduated from Clyde Savannah and went two years to Finger Lakes Community College and got my Associates Degree in Criminal Justice. I then went on to SUNY Oswego and got my Bachelor's Degree in Criminal Justice. Once I was done with school, I went and worked for Seneca Cayuga ARC for about a year. I then took a job and worked for Wayne ARC for 3 years. In 2015, I took the civil service test and began working in the Wayne County Jail as a Corrections Officer. After 6 months, I then went on to the Finger Lakes Law Enforcement Academy and started my position with the Wayne County Sheriff's Office.

Substitute Teacher & Tutor Training, December 4 & 5, 2019

This two day workshop is designed for people wishing to secure a position as a substitute teacher and/or one-on-one tutor position throughout Ontario, Wayne, Seneca and Yates counties and within our W-FL BOCES programs. If you have questions or for more information call Pam @ 315-332-7457 or email: Christine.Bennett@wflboces.org

post_text:
Hello Williamson Central Families!
We wanted to re-share this video that shows you how to navigate around in Schoology. Schoology is a new tool we are using to boost home/school communication. With Schoology, parents and students can access assignments and grades ANYTIME, not just at 5 and 10 weeks. This year, we are using Schoology as the tool for parents to check their child‚Äôs progress whenever they‚Äôd like, including at the 5 week mark when we traditionally sent interim reports. We encourage you to reach out to your child‚Äôs teacher if you have any questions about your child‚Äôs grades. You can email, call or use the Schoology message icon. Our teachers are always happy to communicate at a deeper level. Schoology is just a tool that allows you to check in whenever it is convenient. As with anything new, we are all learning and will continue to monitor and adjust. We are always happy to hear your feedback. It helps us be better.
